orary assumptions and fears about masculinity and femininity were both reflected and reinforced by the local courts. KAREN JONES is an Associate Research Fellow of the University of Greenwich.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCrimexHistoryy15th centuryzEnglandzKent. 0aCrimexHistoryy16th centuryzEnglandzKent. 0aSex rolexHistoryy15th centuryzEnglandzKent. 0aSex rolexHistoryy16th centuryzEnglandzKent. 4aMedieval History. 4aWomen's & Gender Studies. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781846154690?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846154690423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846154690/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles